                         VISN1 Home Causeway St. CBOC

Photo of Boston Outpatient Clinic building Causeway Street CBOC
                                                                 251 Causeway Street
                                                                  Boston, MA 02114
                                                                Phone: (617) 248-1000
                                                                 Fax: (617) 248-1406

                                                                   Practice Hours:
                                                              8:00am - 4:30pm, Mon-Fri

                                             Directions

      The clinic offers a broad spectrum of primary and specialty care
   services provided by staff physicians and nurse practitioners. Patients
   are assigned to a primary care provider team who coordinates their care
     and any necessary referrals to sub-specialty care. A full range of
    laboratory, radiology, pharmacy and EMG services are available. Also
   offered at the clinic are outpatient substance abuse and mental health
     services. The downtown Boston location allows easy access to public
     transportation utilized by a significant percentage of the patients
    treated at the clinic. Hourly shuttle service is provided between the
                    clinic and the Jamaica Plain campus.

                                 DIRECTIONS:
   Public Transportation: Take the Orange Line or the Green Line to North
     Station and walk one block north to the corner of Causeway St. and
                            North Washington Ave.

     From south of Boston: take 93(N) to the Causeway St. Exit, and turn
            right onto Causeway St. VA Clinic is one block north.

   From north of Boston: take 93(S) to Haymarket Exit and follow signs for
     the Fleet Center. The Causeway St. Clinic is one block north of the
                     Fleet center, also on Causeway St.
